  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: 1.9.20-stable\r\nOS & Version: Ubuntu 18.04 LTS\r\nCommit hash : `979fc96899c77876e15807005eadd936da17b6c2`\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nOn Ctrl-C pressed while `geth` is running, `geth` takes some time to save sync progress to disc, and shuts down after that.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nOn Ctrl-C pressed while `geth` is running, `geth` stops immediately.\r\nUpon restart, it needs to sync ~3 days worth of blocks.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\nRun `geth 1.9.20-stable`, sync chain, press Ctrl-C.\r\nMight not be reproducible 100% of the time, sometimes `geth` does save progress to disc.\r\n",
